Perch is one of those timeless LA gems that never goes out of style — perched (literally) on the 15th floor in the heart of Downtown, offering some of the dreamiest skyline views in the city 🌇 The cozy Parisian vibes, string lights, crackling fireplaces, and live jazz make it feel like a mini getaway—even on a Monday night.

Their Monday Night Pairing Menu is such a unique way to enjoy it all — a thoughtful lineup of French-inspired dishes paired with wine and live music from the Molly Miller Quartet. I honestly loved everything, but the escargot stole the show 🐌 So buttery, rich, and flavorful—it disappeared in seconds. The caviar was equally luxe, beautifully plated and perfectly matched with a chilled glass of rosé.

If you’re in the mood to elevate your weeknight plans, this one’s absolutely worth reserving.

@perchlosangeles
📍 448 S Hill St, Los Angeles, CA
🕰️ Mondays only | Live jazz starts at 7 PM

@yakiyausa in Pasadena is THE spot if you’re craving an elevated happy hour experience without the splurge ✨ Sleek, modern yakiniku vibes with an intimate feel, it’s perfect for catching up with friends or easing into date night.

We popped in for their happy hour and every bite was a winner 🏆 The Scallop Crudo was light and refreshing, almost melting on the tongue. The Bone Marrow Toast was so rich and buttery, the marrow was soaking into  the crispy bread. And can’t forget their A5 Japanese Wagyu Tataki… silky, savory perfection in every bite. 

But the Butcher Box was easily my favorite from the happy hour menu: 6 oz of chef’s choice premium cuts that are marbled beautifully. Such a good deal for the quality you’re getting.

The cocktails were just as enjoyable. We tried the Fog on Mt Fuji (yuzu + strawberry + topped off with a bubble), The Royale (a martini topped with Kaluga caviar, so extra in the best way), The Skytree (floral and refreshing with lychee and lavender bitters), and the showstopper Golden Old Fashioned - tableside torched marshmallow and a diamond edition whiskey 🔥🥃

📍3455 E Foothill Blvd, Pasadena, CA 91107
📍17188 Colima Rd. Hacienda Heights, CA 91745

⏰ Happy Hour times at both locations = Monday-Friday: 4:30-6pm, 9pm-10pm

For more foodie adventures, follow @superanitaa! 🥩✨🍸

If you’re looking for a night full of flavor and flair, Lagos in Downtown Fullerton is the spot. 🔥 From the fiery tomahawk steak carved tableside to the vibrant margarita flight that’s almost too pretty to drink, every dish and sip felt like a celebration. We feasted on juicy steak, tender chicken, scallops, and shrimp — and trust me, you’ll want to try the enchiladas too. Finished it all off with their dreamy trio cake... and I’m still thinking about it. 🌟

@lagosmexicancuisine
📍139 W Santa Fe Ave. Fullerton, CA 92832
🚗 Plenty of free parking

I got my head tatted! 😱💆🏻‍♀️✨ well.. sort of.
It’s a trending Korean technique called Scalp Painting, and I’m so glad I did it.

⭐️ WHAT IS SCALP PAINTING?
It’s a non-invasive treatment that uses tiny pigment dots + scalp ampoules to create the look of natural hair follicles—like makeup for your scalp!

Perfect for anyone who regularly uses hair powder to fill in thinning spots.
✔️ Lasts at least 1 year
✔️ Doesn’t cause hair loss or clog pores
✔️ More affordable, faster, and gentler than traditional SMP (scalp tattooing)
✔️ Looks super natural

@beautydesigner_j
💬 Pain level? 2/10 without numbing cream
🧴 You’ll get some flaking after your first wash, but it goes away after 2–3 washes. No downtime
📍 8560 Beach Blvd #104, Buena Park, CA

Huge shoutout to Jennifer—she did an amazing job! I’m already feeling so much more confident 💁🏻‍♀️
She is the first to introduce scalp painting in the U.S.!

I took a class at @lecharme.beauteboutique and it completely changed the way I apply makeup 💄✨ They walk you through every step, then have you wipe it all off and do it yourself—so the technique really sticks. I’ve taken three classes now, and I learn something new every single time!

Whether you’re a total beginner or just want to refine your skills, I highly recommend it!

✨ Bilingual Instruction – Classes are available in both English & Vietnamese
✨ All Makeup & Skincare Provided – Just show up and everything’s ready for you

📍7862 Warner Ave, STE A, Huntington Beach, CA 92647

HiroNori Craft Ramen

Say hello to a sweet little cloud of happiness ☁️💗 Cloud 9’s Strawberry Cotton Candy is finally landing in LA—available for a limited time at select Costco stores in the LA region!

It’s their first-ever LA launch, so don’t wait too long to snag a pack (or two). Each multi-pack comes with individually wrapped servings, made with real freeze-dried strawberries and just 25 calories per pack 🍓🍬

Perfect for sharing with friends, treating the kids, or keeping all to yourself 🩷✨ It’s the kind of sweet you’ll want to stock up on this summer.
